  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX spot at 6591.75 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6596 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and should be buying this dip toward the 6590 support wall. The massive positive gamma concentration at 6600 (+117M) creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any push higher, while the 6575 negative gamma pocket (-16M) represents the key support level where dealer buying accelerates. The recent wall break and GEX surge (70% in 5 minutes) indicates heightened options activity, but the thick positive gamma walls from 6590-6610 should contain volatility and promote mean reversion within this range.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6590-6600 with limited breakout potential in either direction.",
